  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the sliced red onion and cook until golden brown, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the sliced red bell pepper and cook for an additional 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add the sliced zucchini and cherry tomatoes, and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the chopped artichoke hearts, sun-dried tomatoes, minced garlic, and cooked vegetables to the skillet.",
    "Stir in the light rum and cook for 1-2 minutes, until the liquid has reduced slightly.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Transfer the skillet to the oven and bake at 400°F for 15-20 minutes, or until the top is crispy.",
    "Remove the skillet from the oven and top with crumbled feta cheese and chopped fresh parsley.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
  ],
